
    Section 1 - Boot Process and System Logging
  - BIOS
    - is OS independent.
    - Performs the POST(Power on Self Test), checks hardware components, only proceeds if successful.
    - Knows of bootable devices, hard drives, usb drives, dvd drives etc.
  - BootLoader
    - Start the OS.
  - initrd(Initial RAM disk)
    - Temporary filesystem loaded into memory when system boots.
  - /boot
    - Contains the files required to boot linux. initrd, kernel, boot loader config.
  - Kernel ring buffer
    - Contains messages from the linux kernel.
    - /var/log/dmesg or dmesg command to view.
  - Systemd
    - Specify targets to configure linux run level (single user, multi user, reboot etc)
    - /lib/systemd/system

  - Linux uses the syslog standard.
  - syslog config is /etc/rsyslog.conf
